message.content:
The time taken for a pair of socks to dry depends on many factors including humidity, temperature and other environmental variables. However, in your scenario where you have 10 pairs of wet socks that took 10 hours to dry, it means each pair of socks took approximately 1 hour (or 6 minutes) to dry.

If we assume the same weather conditions as before, Tom will need roughly 7 hours (or 42 minutes) to dry seven pairs of socks. This is assuming that all the other factors remain constant and are not affected by the number of socks being dried.
